rComments: Take his section of polisci 1020e if you want to do well in later years in the program. Experienced, super informed and brings great examples from many parts of the world. He cares deeply about what you do with your polisci. He is the go-to-person if you are thinking about grad or law school or work in diplomacy/foreign affairs after King's.

Great course.  You will learn incredibly useful negotiations/lifelong skills.  Take this course irrespective of your major if you can get in.. The only downside is that the course fills up unbelievably quickly and good luck if you think someone will drop out for you to get in. His accent was not an issue in this class.
he cares, good teacher! accent but we're in Canada, you should be used to it by now.

Can speak for 2 hours without a break, but you won't understand a word he says due to his thick accent. Brought his kid to class. Would be a better teacher if he didn't think so highly of himself. Would not recommend class at all.
teacherRatingTags: ['Lecture heavy', 'Tough grader', "Skip class? You won't pass."]

rComments: + Very knowledgeable and experienced prof, teaching exciting content - Poor delivery and very poor professionalism (Missed more classes than me, 3hr student led lectures for 5-6 months of the year, most minuscule/irrelevant questions on tests, unstructured lectures/powerpoint notes)

The class is 3 hours long, and what we mainly do is have discussions. While discussions are important, i truly believe it's unnecessary to do so for 3 hours! Barely ever holds a lecture and when he does we never finish his slides and are peobably about 2 slides into his entire 30 slide powerpoint. Discussions can be extremely boring and repetitive.
teacherRatingTags: ['Beware of pop quizzes', 'Tough grader', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: One of the best courses you will take in Univeristy? Materials and prof are great. Interesting discussions every week. The prof is super open minded and will challenge you to think outside of the box. Your views will likely change by the  end of the course. Must take course if interested in development and international affairs.

The most organized, well-designed course I have taken in university. He has accent but you will hear him clearly by second week if you are not mentally lazy. The prof knows material inside out. Must take course if thinking about grad school. He will help you find suitable program and get you into it if you are  a serious  student.
Hard class, cannot understand accent, makes up words, spellcheck was unimpressed
Very helpful! One of the nicest and memorable professors I've had.
The worst prof imaginable. Drop-drop-drop.
Agree with the guy. What I didn't like how he discourages students to pursue with the course.. Come on.
Lecture are confusing. Marking is hard. Accent is crazy. Don't recommend.

Well organized lectures with slides. I appreciated his non-eurocentric approach. Attend the lectures and skim thru the readings you'll be fine. He gives good advice on pursuing careers in IR & grad school.  And he's a soccer guy, how can you not like him.  Caution: TAs are relatively tough markers.

He is the Best Professor I have ever had. He is funny, smart and makes you want to learn. Go to class and read the textbook and you can get a good mark. He is very fair so the amount of work you put in is the mark you will get. I hope to take another class taught by him.
A decent professor who makes an earnest effort to teach and connect with students. Tests are fair, but most students still average around 72%. You get what you deserve in his courses, good or bad.

He is an amazing prof. Very friendly and always willing to lend a helping hand. He's lectures are organized and he is always prepared. The TAs on the other hand not so friendly and very moody and HARD MARKERS. He told us your TAs are here to help you, let's just say they are there trying very hard to FAIL YOU! But you will still manage to beat them

This was the best course I took this year. Prof Tieku is so enthusiatic and clear which makes the class a truly enjoyable experience. He's extremely approachable and always willing to lend a helping hand. I felt that it was the only class that challenged me in first year and I can say I walked away with a better understanding of Africa

Tieku is an excellent professor. At first it was difficult understanding his African accent, but come second class I had no problem understanding him. His class is not easy, but so worthwhile! I learned SO much. And he's great at responding to any questions. Very approachable and helpful.

Absolutely great prof. Approachable, bloody clever, open to new ideas. Not an easy marker, but completely fair. Has clear expectations, set out at the beginning of class, and is willing to discuss what they entail. A great choice, esp. for Trin1 or African Studies.

Professor Tieku is an excellent professor. He is not an easy marker, but he will prepare you for top level university courses with the level of rigor and academic excellence his teaching style exacts.
